Interesting valuation debate happening w $PTON. Some use sum-of-parts method. Eg, take FY22 estimates - ($3.8B HW @ 2x = $7.6B) + ($1.4B Sub Rev @ 10x = $14B) = $22B versus $40B mkt cap

Others forecast P&L. Eg, focus on path to 50M subs @ $20 ARPU @ 7x = $84B mkt cap (plus HW)

Another for a high growth co is to use Price/Sales * multiple
In this case 
FY2021 = $4B * 10 = $40B
FY2022 = $7B * 8 = $56B
FY2023 = $10.5B * 6.5 = $68B

Plug in your own in Rev forecast and multiple. Bull case not that hard for long term holders.
